@page "/tutorial"
@using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations

<PageTitle>Blazor Tutorial</PageTitle>

<div class="container-narrow">
  <h1>Blazor Tutorial</h1>
  <p class="text-muted">Target time: ~45–60 minutes. You’ll create a WASM app, add a form, and deploy to GitHub Pages.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
    <ul class="mb-0">
      <li>.NET 8 SDK</li>
      <li>GitHub account</li>
      <li>Coding Environment</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>1) Create & run the app</h3>
    <p>Open the terminal of your preferred coding environment, such as <vscode>Visual Studio Code</vscode>. And enter:</p>
    <div class="code-block">
      <pre><code>dotnet new blazorwasm -n BlazorDemo -f net8.0
cd BlazorDemo
dotnet run</code></pre>
    </div>
    <p>Browse <kbd>https://localhost:5001</kbd> and verify the template loads.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>2) Add a form with validation</h3>
    <p>Open <code>Pages/Counter.razor</code> and replace with:</p>
    <div class="code-block">
      <pre><code>@@page "/counter"

&lt;h1&gt;Counter&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;EditForm Model="@model" OnValidSubmit="Submit"&gt;
  &lt;DataAnnotationsValidator /&gt;
  &lt;ValidationSummary /&gt;

  &lt;div class="mb-3"&gt;
    &lt;label class="form-label"&gt;Name&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;InputText class="form-control" @@bind-Value="model.Name" /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;button class="btn btn-brand" type="submit"&gt;Submit&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/EditForm&gt;

@code {
    MyModel model = new();

    void Submit() { /* handle */ }

    class MyModel { [Required] public string? Name { get; set; } }
}
</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>3) Deploy to GitHub Pages</h3>
    <p>Publish and push using the provided workflow (see <code>deploy.yml</code>).</p>
    <div class="code-block">
      <pre><code>dotnet publish -c Release -o publish
# Commit & push; GH Actions will build and deploy</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="text-muted">Tip: Add screenshots of each step (build, run, live site) to score highly on clarity.</p>
</div>